---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn what VibeOps Forum is and how the community works for AI builders."
>
  <section class="shell grid gap-10 py-20 md:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr]">
    <div>
      <p class="mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-teal-200">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-balance text-5xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.06em] text-white md:text-6xl">
        A forum for the people operating the next software stack.
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-vibe max-w-3xl">
      <p>
        VibeOps Forum is a Slack community for builders working with AI coding agents, agent operations, A2A protocol ideas, and MCP tooling. The community is for people who want to compare real workflows, not only read announcements.
      </p>
      <p>
        Members share demos, failures, architecture notes, prompts, agent traces, and production lessons. The common thread is practical ownership: AI tools can accelerate work, but builders still need clear design, review, testing, and operational judgment.
      </p>
      <h2>How the community works</h2>
      <p>
        Bring an artifact and a question. A useful post might include a repository, a tool server, a design sketch, a failing agent run, or a short explanation of a workflow that made a build faster or safer.
      </p>
      <h2>Who should join</h2>
      <p>
        Join if you are building products with coding agents, designing agent workflows, evaluating A2A patterns, creating MCP integrations, or trying to understand how AI-assisted software work changes engineering practice.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="accent-link" href={SITE.slackUrl}>Join the VibeOps Slack</a> and introduce yourself with what you are building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
